snippet: Abdiaziz Abdinur Ibrahim was jailed in January for interviewing a woman who said she was gang-raped by government soldiers, in a case that sparked international condemnation.
abstract: Somali court frees journalist Abdiaziz Abdinur Ibrahim, who was jailed in January for interviewing a woman who said she was gang-raped by government soldiers; case has sparked international condemnation.
lead_paragraph: Abdiaziz Abdinur Ibrahim was jailed in January for interviewing a woman who said she was gang-raped by government soldiers, in a case that sparked international condemnation.
